#. <section class="sutta" id="sn16.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn16.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 16"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 16"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.12:0.2"
msgid "1. Kassapavagga"
msgstr "1. Kassapa"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 12. Paraṃmaraṇasutta → tathāgataparammaraṇasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn16.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Paraṃmaraṇasutta"
msgstr "12. The Realized One After Death"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.223"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn16.12:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca mahākassapo āyasmā ca sāriputto bārāṇasiyaṃ viharanti "
"isipatane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Mahākassapa and Venerable Sāriputta were staying near "
"Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana."

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā "
"mahākassapo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā mahākassapena saddhiṃ "
"sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to "
"Venerable Mahākassapa, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to Mahākassapa:"

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.4"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, āvuso kassapa, hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti?"
msgstr "“Reverend Kassapa, does a Realized One exist after death?”"

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.5"
msgid "“Abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā:"
msgstr "“Reverend, this has not been declared by the Buddha.”"

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.6"
msgid "‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.7"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti?"
msgstr "“Well then, does a Realized One not exist after death?”"

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.8"
msgid "“Evampi kho, āvuso, abyākataṃ bhagavatā:"
msgstr "“This too has not been declared by the Buddha.”"

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.9"
msgid "‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.10"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti?"
msgstr "“Well then, does a Realized One both exist and not exist after death?”"

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.11"
msgid "“Abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā:"
msgstr "“This too has not been declared by the Buddha.”"

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.12"
msgid "‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.13"
msgid "“Kiṃ panāvuso, neva hoti, na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well then, does a Realized One neither exist nor not exist after death?”"

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.14"
msgid "“Evampi kho, āvuso, abyākataṃ bhagavatā:"
msgstr "“This too has not been declared by the Buddha.”"

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.15"
msgid "‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.16"
msgid "“Kasmā cetaṃ, āvuso, abyākataṃ bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr "“And why has this not been declared by the Buddha?”"

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.17"
msgid ""
"“Na hetaṃ, āvuso, atthasaṃhitaṃ nādibrahmacariyakaṃ na nibbidāya na virāgāya "
"na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"“Because it’s not beneficial or relevant to the fundamentals of the "
"spiritual life. It doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, "
"peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "sn16.12:1.18"
msgid "Tasmā taṃ abyākataṃ bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr "That’s why it has not been declared by the Buddha.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn16.12:2.1"
msgid "“Atha kiñcarahāvuso, byākataṃ bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr "“So what now has been declared by the Buddha?”"

# Odd punctuation choice in text.
msgctxt "sn16.12:2.2"
msgid "“Idaṃ ‘dukkhan’ti kho, āvuso, byākataṃ bhagavatā;"
msgstr "“‘This is suffering’ has been declared by the Buddha."

msgctxt "sn16.12:2.3"
msgid "ayaṃ ‘dukkhasamudayo’ti byākataṃ bhagavatā;"
msgstr "‘This is the origin of suffering’ …"

msgctxt "sn16.12:2.4"
msgid "ayaṃ ‘dukkhanirodho’ti byākataṃ bhagavatā;"
msgstr "‘This is the cessation of suffering’ …"

msgctxt "sn16.12:2.5"
msgid "ayaṃ ‘dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti byākataṃ bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’ has been "
"declared by the Buddha.”"

msgctxt "sn16.12:2.6"
msgid "“Kasmā cetaṃ, āvuso, byākataṃ bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr "“And why has this been declared by the Buddha?”"

msgctxt "sn16.12:2.7"
msgid ""
"“Etañhi, āvuso, atthasaṃhitaṃ etaṃ ādibrahmacariyakaṃ etaṃ nibbidāya "
"virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"“Because it’s beneficial and relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual "
"life. It leads to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, "
"awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "sn16.12:2.8"
msgid "Tasmā taṃ byākataṃ bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr "That’s why it has been declared by the Buddha.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn16.12:2.9"
msgid "Dvādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
